post_text:
Due to Covid-19 we are not able to use our classroom instruments for music class this year. Students will be making instrument kits made with found sounds so we have something to play. This is where we need your help!!! If you have any of the following things laying around that you no longer need and would like to donate them to the music department, we would greatly appreciate it.
Ice cream buckets or coffee cans with lid
plastic Easter eggs
McDonalds kids milk containers (washed!!)
small dowels, old drum sticks, new pencils, new chopsticks
new pool noodles
bag of rice, popcorn, beans, peas, small beads
decorative tape
ribbed tubing cut 4" pieces
Gallon baggies
Items can be dropped off at the music room during open house or left in the entryway of the school with a sign ATTN: MUSIC DEPT.
Thank you for helping us out during this uncertain time!
Mrs. Nordine and Mrs. Tange

Typically, North Star provides electrical safety demonstrations in the classrooms across our service territory. What students normally learn is:

‚Ä¢ Stay away from power lines
‚Ä¢ Don‚Äôt fly kites near power lines
‚Ä¢ Remind your parents to watch out for power lines when
they are using a ladder, chainsaw, or other outdoor
equipment.
‚Ä¢ Never use anything with a cord or plug around water.
‚Ä¢ Keep metal objects out of toasters
‚Ä¢ Don‚Äôt climb trees near power lines

Let‚Äôs make this FUN in a different way! Help your students record a 5-10 second movie clip telling the world about how to be safe around electricity.

Email the clip to nsec@wiktel.com . The best clip will earn the wining student and $50!
